						               													<description>This is the 2nd installment for the Avalon Hill miniatures based game of Napoleon's Battles. It is a 54-pages Booklet with 'Errata' &amp;amp; clarifications for the 1st game, additional Terrain features, with 9 more Scenarios, the Divisional Armies Structured Army Charts, Additional Optional Rules, even MORE labels for these Scenarios, a set of BLANK 'generic' Officers labels and a BLANK information chart for further uses.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Scenarios covered in this are: &amp;#10;S-9.The Battle of Valmy, Sept.20,1792; &amp;#10;S-10.The Battle of Friedland, June 14,1807; &amp;#10;S-11.The Battle of Corunna, Jan.16,1809; &amp;#10;S-12.The Battle of Aspern-Essling, May 21~22,1809; &amp;#10;S-13.The Battle of Ocano, Sept.19,1809; &amp;#10;S-14.The Battle of Salamanca, July 22,1812; &amp;#10;S-15.The Battle of Leipzig, Oct.16~19,1813; &amp;#10;S-16.The Battle of Craonne, Mar.7,1814; &amp;#10;S-17.-A 400 Point Demonstration Game-1814.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Most of the 'Battles' covered here involve a single gaming table while the S-12.Aspern-Essling battle uses 2 tables and the S-15.Leipzig battle has 4-(!) tables being used for it's playing.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
